# {{APP_NAME}}

A Vastu application. Built on the Vastu framework — enterprise workspace, auth, and data engine included.

## Quick start

```bash
# From the monorepo root
pnpm install

# Set up environment
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your DATABASE_URL and other secrets

# Run database migrations
pnpm --filter @app/{{APP_NAME}} prisma:migrate

# Seed the database (base data + domain data)
pnpm --filter @app/{{APP_NAME}} prisma:seed

# Start the dev server
pnpm --filter @app/{{APP_NAME}} dev
```

Then open [http://localhost:3001](http://localhost:3001).

Default credentials (from base seed):
- Admin: `admin@vastu.dev` / any password
- Editor: `editor@vastu.dev` / any password
- Viewer: `viewer@vastu.dev` / any password

## Project structure

```
apps/{{APP_NAME}}/
├── prisma/
│   ├── schema.prisma     # Database schema (base + domain models)
│   └── seed.ts           # Seed script (calls base seed, then domain seed)
├── src/
│   ├── app/              # Next.js App Router pages
│   │   ├── layout.tsx    # Root layout
│   │   ├── page.tsx      # Redirects to /workspace
│   │   └── workspace/
│   │       └── page.tsx  # Workspace shell mount point
│   ├── pages.ts          # Page registrations (sidebar pages)
│   └── formatters.ts     # Custom cell formatters
├── next.config.mjs       # Next.js config
├── tsconfig.json         # TypeScript config (extends root)
└── README.md             # This file
```

## Extending the schema

Add your domain tables to `prisma/schema.prisma` below the domain section marker.
Then run:

```bash
pnpm --filter @app/{{APP_NAME}} prisma:migrate
```

## Registering pages

Edit `src/pages.ts` to add pages to the sidebar:

```typescript
import { PageRegistry } from '@vastu/workspace';

PageRegistry.register({
  id: 'my-page',
  name: 'My Page',
  icon: 'IconTable',
  template: 'table-listing',
  section: 'PAGES',
  order: 1,
  config: { table: 'MyModel', columns: [...] },
});
```

## Adding custom formatters

Edit `src/formatters.ts` to register custom cell display formatters:

```typescript
import { FormatterRegistry } from '@vastu/workspace';

FormatterRegistry.register('my-formatter', {
  render: (value) => <span>{value}</span>,
  export: (value) => String(value),
});
```

